Abstract:
. Let Ω be an open subset of RN, and let p, q : Ω → [1, ∞] be
measurable functions. We give a necessary and suﬃcient condition for
the embedding of the variable exponent space Lp(·) (Ω) in Lq(·) (Ω) to
be almost compact. This leads to a condition on Ω, p and q suﬃcient to
ensure that the Sobolev space W 1,p(·) (Ω) based on Lp(·) (Ω) is compactly
embedded in Lq(·) (Ω) ; compact embedding results of this type already
in the literature are included as special cases.
